This paper deals with decoding algorithms for subspace codes, which are a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper specifically focuses on twisted Gabidulin codes, which are a type of error-correcting code (cs.CC). The paper also discusses linear codes over finite fields, which is a topic in cryptography (cs.CR) and coding theory (cs.DS). Finally, the paper may be relevant to signal processing (cs.SI) due to its focus on decoding algorithms.
